<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">585.61B1/596: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-09">August 9,
                                    1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3053. Department’s 3014, 7th. The President has today issued a
                                proclamation declaring the load line convention suspended for the
                                duration of the present emergency.<note n="39" xml:id="d498fn39">For
                                    text of proclamation and public announcement issued August 9,
                                    1941, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                                    August 9, 1941, p. 114; see also 55 Stat. 1660.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>